        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "distinguishing features"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                161,
                498,
                322,
                514
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Inflexible, rigid star with thick, solid, spongy disc. Pentagonal in shape. Marginal plates indistinct. Distinct madreporite. Fine raised bumps (sheaths of adambulacral spines) form distinct rows along each arm, but no spines apparent. Thick fleshy starfish with smooth aboral and oral surface. Double rows of tube feet. No marginal plates visible. Patterning on aboral surface can be very distinct when brooding (see third image)."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                161,
                514,
                489,
                644
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Colour"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                163,
                656,
                211,
                670
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Bright pink to orange on aboral; pale yellow on oral surface."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                161,
                671,
                487,
                701
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Size"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                163,
                714,
                194,
                730
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Can reach up to 230 mm diameter."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                161,
                731,
                386,
                745
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "distribution"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                510,
                498,
                596,
                513
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "South African endemic. West and South Coasts of South Africa; from 400 to 1 000+ m depth."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                509,
                513,
                836,
                544
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Similar species"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                509,
                556,
                615,
                571
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Spoladaster veneris, but Chondraster ellatosis does not inflate and is more leathery."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                509,
                571,
                835,
                602
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
